(
 "Congratulations, you've mastered structural editing! Here's your cheat sheet:

Join   (Alt+→):  Expand parens to grab the next item
Leave  (Alt+←):  Shrink parens to release the last item
Shed   (Alt+↑):  Remove the enclosing parens entirely
Split  (Alt+↓):  Split one group into two at the cursor

These four moves, combined with typing parentheses and deleting, let you reshape any expression while keeping your code balanced at all times.

Structural editing has more advanced maneuvers to be even more efficient, such as deleting an entire parenthetical or skipping between them. Check out the help page for a complete list.

Happy structural editing!
")
